                How to prepare for your new dog:
            </h2>
            <h2
                class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-[#3f3f40] text-start mb-2 md:mb-4 wow animate__animated animate__zoomIn">
                5 things you must do
            </h2>
            <p class="mb-4 font-normal text-[#3f3f40] text-sm md:text-base text-justify">Adopting a dog is exciting, but
                it can often mean a big life change for you and them. To make things easier and give your new dog the
                best chance of settling in, it’s really important to prepare for their arrival.</p>
            <p class="mb-4 md:mb-6 font-normal text-[#3f3f40] text-sm md:text-base text-justify">As well as having a
                moral duty
                to look after your new dog properly, you have a legal responsibility. Under the Animal Welfare Act, you
                must give your dog:</p>

            <ul class="max-w-md space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-[#3f3f40]">
                <li class="text-lg p-0 m-0">
                    <span class="text-base">A suitable place to live</span>
                </li>
                <li class="text-lg p-0 m-0">
                    <span class="text-base">A healthy diet and access to clean water</span>
                </li>
                <li class=" text-lg p-0 m-0">
                    <span class="text-base">The ability to behave normally</span>
                </li>
                <li class="text-lg p-0 m-0">
                    <span class="text-base">Appropriate company</span>
                </li>
                <li class="text-lg p-0 m-0">
                    <span class="text-base">Protection from pain, injury, suffering and disease</span>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <p class="mt-4 md:mt-6 font-normal text-[#3f3f40] text-sm md:text-base text-justify">So, to help you get
                ready for the big day and understand your legal responsibilities as a dog owner, we’ve created this ‘to
                do’ list.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- point 1 - cat -->
        <div
